# K3 semantics: Strong Kleene three-valued logic
# Designated value: T only.  Third value I = "indeterminate".
#
# Key result: P or not P is NOT a K3 tautology.
# When P=I, not P = I (mirror), and I or I = I, which is not designated.

tautology? P or not P

# The set of reachable values shows I can appear:
evaluate P or not P

# Modus ponens is still valid:
entails P -> Q, P |- Q

# But P -> P is also not a tautology (P=I gives I->I = I):
tautology? P -> P
